      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "```javascript\nconst { chromium } = require('playwright');\n\n(async () => {\n  const browser = await chromium.launch();\n  const context = await browser.newContext();\n  const page = await context.newPage();\n\n  // Test Login Flow\n  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/login');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"username\"]', 'testuser');\n  await page.fill('input[name=\"password\"]', 'password');\n  await page.click('button[type=\"submit\"]');\n  await page.waitForSelector('div.dashboard');\n\n  // Test Dashboard Loading\n  await page.waitForSelector('div.dashboard');\n  await page.waitForSelector('div.checkout');\n\n  // Test Checkout Completion\n  await page.click('div.checkout');\n  await page.waitForSelector('div.checkout-complete');\n\n  await browser.close();\n})();\n```\nThis script covers the login, dashboard loading, and checkout completion. It uses Playwright to automate the browser and interact with the web app. The script navigates to the login page, enters the username and password, and clicks the submit button. It then waits for the dashboard to load and for the checkout button to appear. Finally, it clicks the checkout button and waits for the checkout completion",
